	   <tr><td colspan=2>Not sure if I follow you - but I think you're saying that you want to get a full set of black pantherskin armor.&nbsp;&nbsp;I looked at this stuff, and besides the fact that I've never seen anyone wearing it or selling it, I don't think it's all that special.  Sure, it gets you great stats, but look at the measely 8 AC and 10 hp you're gaining from it.  And you're obviously overweight and losing AC as a result.  You don't list what you're wearing now, but replacing a couple heavy pieces (I'm guessing you're probably wearing heavy boots and/or a heavy chest piece) will recover many more AC than getting this armor.  Plus, none of this stuff has any resists on it at all.<br><br>It's been discussed on these boards quite a bit - you should chase, in order:<br><br>AC<br>Resists<br>HP<br>Stats<br><br>All those great stats won't help you live very long if you have a crummy AC and no resists.<br><br>Black pantherskin is not easy stuff to acquire - you need pelts, some expensive components, and most importantly a super taior friend.  It sounds like you want to buy this stuff - I'd strongly argue against it.  Based on what I see price-wise (allakhazam sez 10k for the chest piece - absurd!) you won't be able to afford any of it for a VERY long time, and there is MUCH better gear out there for FAR less money.  If you post your current gear, the monks on this board will surely give you recommendations that will be far better uses of your hard-earned cash.<br><br>Feign Death skill goes up as (lvl*5)+5.  So at your level it maxes out at 110.  Increase it by practicing - CONSTANTLY.  On a boat, when grouped on med breaks or even between mobs if you're not pulling, during some non-combat time, just keep pounding that key.  Make a hot-key for it, and put a SIT hot key right next to it in your hotkey bank.<br><br>I believe Ykesha is a 70 point Direct Damage starting at level 40.<br><br>Hunting for money is always a question.  I made decent cash in South Karana, but had to run to and from High Keep bank a LOT.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 49th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro<br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a><br>Dripsy - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922</a></td></tr>
